<TEXT>
a couple who reported their 7yearold son 
missing were charged monday with child abuse after the bruised and 
malnourished boy was found on a subway car with cigarette burns and 
black eyes police said 
rene samacarit 28 and zorida maldonado 31 of brooklyn were 
charged with seconddegree assault and endangering the welfare of a 
minor said police spokesman sgt raymond odonnell 
the couple reported the boy missing at 230 pm less than half 
an hour later transit police found the malnourished and beaten 
child on a subway in manhattan odonnell said 
the boy who had run away from home was taken to st vincents 
hospital with multiple injuries including cigarette burns bruises 
black eyes a throat infection and malnutrition odonnell said 
his parents identified him at the hospital and were charged 
following an investigation odonnell said 
the boys 3yearold sister has been turned over to the bureau of 
child welfare odonnell said 
the childrens names were not released 
