<TEXT>
when donald kowalski retired from the 
backbreaking life of a miner on minnesotas iron range he looked 
forward to years of peace and leisure 
instead the 58yearold kowalski and his wife della are 
spending their golden years at war with a lesbian professor over who 
should care for their severely braindamaged daughter sharon 
the professor karen thompson says she deserves to be ms 
kowalskis caretaker because the two secretly considered themselves 
married before ms kowalski was paralyzed in a 1983 automobile crash 
caused by a drunken driver 
kowalski and his wife say the claim is bogus they insist 
thompsons interest in their daughter centers on money thompson has 
generated by publicizing the case in speeches across the country and 
a book 
i hate her with a passion kowalski said from his home in 
rural nashwauk in northeastern minnesota i cant picture an end 
to this 
thompson says the money is intended to help ms kowalski and she 
questions her parents motives they would rather she be a 
vegetable than a lesbian she said until sharons rights are 
protected i will fight this 
thompson who has become a national spokeswoman for gay and 
lesbian rights has helped establish two funds for her friend and 
organized rallies in 21 us cities in august to observe free 
sharon kowalski day 
according to court records the two women had lived together for 
four years ms kowalski 32 who was a high school physical 
education teacher had named thompson 41 as the beneficiary of her 
50000 life insurance policy before the accident 
the courts have acknowledged the relationship but have kept 
kowalski as his daughters guardian giving him power to make 
decisions for her and initially allowing him to deny thompson 
visiting privileges 
but in december a judge ordered a reevaluation of ms kowalski 
to determine how soundly she thinks and whether she is capable of 
making decisions about her own care 
ms kowalski who is in a nursing home near nashwauk has lost 
the use of her limbs and is unable to speak but can use the fingers 
of her right hand and communicates by typing shaking her head and 
using an alphabet board 
under the judges new order anyone is allowed to see her if she 
reliably requested to see them ms thompson said she was 
granted supervised visits because ms kowalski asked to see her in 
interviews with a psychiatrist 
a week ago the two visited over four days for the first time in 
3 years 
i think sharon is soon going to let everyone know that she can 
control her own future thompson said from ms kowalskis bedside 
she smiles and she chuckles and she has responded so well shes 
been happy to see me 
after the reevaluation the judge could go as far as declaring 
ms kowalski competent to handle her own affairs but her parents 
say such a finding would be impossible they say thompson has 
exaggerated ms kowalskis mental abilities and her chances for 
rehabilitation 
were never going to have the real sharon kowalski back said 
her mother you might get a good response from sharon one day and 
the next day nothing it would take a miracle to see her recover 
thompson who teaches physical education at st cloud state 
university said ms kowalski wants to go home with her to st 
cloud the kowalskis say their daughter has never expressed that 
desire to them 
thompson said she could provide better care for ms kowalski 
because she has more talent and education than her parents 
i made a lifetime commitment to sharon and i want to honor 
that thompson said 
ms kowalskis doctor william wilson opposes moving her from 
the nursing home he said home care would be out of the question 
because thompson is not certified to care for someone as severely 
disabled as ms kowalski 
meanwhile thompson admits she has started other relationships 
i have found that there are several people in the world that i 
can have relationships with thompson said but i dont know if 
i can fall deeply in love with another person like i did with 
sharon 
kowalski and thompson say they are likely to be battling each 
other as long as ms kowalski is judged incapable of handling her 
own affairs 
if this keeps up i probably dont have much time left said 
kowalski who has suffered two heart attacks in the past year that 
he attributes to the stress my heart can only take so much 
</TEXT>
