<TEXT>
thousands of people prayed for rain in northern 
italian churches and some parched communities planned religious 
processions hoping to bring an end to one of the worst droughts in 
years 
at 1300 roman catholic churches in the diocese of milan on 
sunday priests invoked the rain that restores the earth and 
air according to the diocese 
churchgoers in bergamo and genoa have also been praying for rain 
as sunny dry weather threatens crops and left ski slopes bare 
several parishes in small towns south of milan were planning 
processions along the adda river if rain did not arrive in the next 
few days the italian news agency ansa reported sunday 
italy has received only half the precipitation it usually gets in 
the septemberjanuary period the milan area has had one rain shower 
since november 24 while genoa has been dry for four months 
the lack of rain has prompted limits on private water use and 
contributed to brush fires that have scorched thousands of acres in 
northern italy 
the dry weather is the result of a highpressure system that has 
remained over the mediterranean for months meteorologists say 
