<TEXT>
barbara harris has taken her place as the first 
woman bishop in church that traces its heritage directly to early 
days of christianity despite a stormy break with catholicism during 
the reign of englands henry viii 
the 28 millionmember us episcopal church developed from the 
church of england and is one of the several independent national 
churches that belong to the worldwide anglican communion 
english settlers brought the church to virginia at the turn of 
the 17th century it became a separate group when it adopted a 
constitution and religious laws and a revision of the book of common 
prayer in philadelphia in 1789 
the church of england had separated from the roman catholic 
church in the 16th century after henry viii was denied an annulment 
to his marriage to catherine of aragon who had no sons 
henry secretly married his second of six wives anne boleyn 
rejected the popes authority in england and appointed thomas 
cranmer archbishop of canterbury cranmer approved henrys annulment 
in 1534 parliament declared that the pope had no authority in 
england and made the church of england a separate institution 
the communion contends that its clergy are directly linked to the 
apostles of christ through an unbroken series of ceremonies other 
denominations claims the same kind of historic succession including 
the roman catholic church 
the episcopal church voted in 1976 to allow women priests since 
then about 1200 have been ordained 
the church is governed by a permanent executive council and by 
the general convention which meets every three years 
</TEXT>
