a mild earthquake early today shook a 
wide area of san francisco the sixth tremor in northern california 
within 24 hours officials said 
no damage or injuries were immediately reported from the quakes 
whose magnitudes ranged from 24 to 30 on the richter scale 
the sixth quake struck at 1201 am and had a magnitude of 30 
on the richter scale according to the united states geological 
surveys national earthquake information center in golden colo 
it was centered west of the golden gate bridge the same area as 
two earlier ones said seisomologist anthony lomax of the university 
of california seismology station 
we had several calls from all over the city but so far no 
reports of damage said a san francisco police dispatcher who 
declined to give his name 
the first quake which measured 27 on the richter scale struck 
at 1149 am sunday and was centered about five miles west of the 
bridge 
within two minutes two more quakes measuring 26 and 24 on the 
richter scale were felt in southern marin county lomax said 
at 10 pm a magnitude 30 quake struck the same general area 
off the golden gate as the first one lomax said 
a quake that measured 29 was centered near san leandro about 10 
miles south of berkeley at 1041 pm he said 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude 
a quake of magnitude 35 can cause slight damage 
the san francisco earthquake of 1906 measured an estimated 83 on 
the richter scale 
