<TEXT>
iran says it will hang 70 drug traffickers 
tuesday the highest number to be executed in one day in that 
nations fierce antinarcotics crackdown aimed at stopping the flow 
to at least 1 million addicts 
hardline prosecutergeneral musavi khoeiniha said in a recent 
radio interview this is the end of the line if we do not destroy 
them drug smugglers they will destroy our youths 
khoeiniha first gained fame in 1979 as the guiding hand behind 
the militant extremists who stormed the us embassy holding 52 
hostages for 444 days 
iran instituted a new law on jan 21 that includes the death 
penalty for anyone found with 30 grams just over an ounce of 
heroin or five kilograms 11 pounds of opium or hashish addicting 
someone else carries a 20year sentence 
the law coincided with a crackdown that put helicopter gunships 
into the air along the borders with pakistan and afghanistan to 
track smugglers 
on jan 16 a record 56 drug smugglers were executed the 
official islamic republic news agency monitored in nicosia says 
105 smugglers have been executed since dec 31 
the iranian resistance group mujahedeen khalq accuses the iranian 
government of creating hysteria over the drug problem as a means of 
extending a siege mentality and eliminating its enemies following 
the 8year iraniraq war 
