tehran and the rest in cities throughout iran 
executions were suspended during a 10day celebration that ended 
feb 11 to mark the 10th anniversary of the revolution that toppled 
the late shah in 1979 
iranian police released statistics monday saying 3300 drug 
traffickers have been arrested in iran since 1987 and 11 metric tons 
of opium 1540 pounds of heroin and 23 metric tons of hashish 
seized 
drug addicts now have six months to kick the habit or face jail 
addiction is not considered a medical problem in iran 
the prosecutorgeneral said if an addicts decision to give up 
his habit is serious he needs nothing else they should not expect 
the government to treat them as patients 
iran has blamed everyone from underground opposition movements to 
the us central intelligence agency for trying to turn iranian 
youth into addicts 
iranians leaving the country said many youths turned to drugs to 
escape the intense pressure they faced to conform to islamic 
principals as iran was reborn as a fundamentalist state 
the draft in the holy war against iraq was another factor 
they said 
iranian press reports concentrate on ways of eliminating drug 
supplies rather than the cause of addiction 
khoeiniha said one way around the death penalty was to turn 
others in 
if they smugglers report themselves repent name old traders 
and cooperate with discovering the rings certainly we will request 
the great leader ayatollah ruhollah khomeini to grant them parole 
otherwise they will be punished according to the law 
