us district court judge alcee l hastings on 
monday asked the senate to dismiss 16 of the 17 articles of 
impeachment returned against him last august by the house of 
representatives 
the 52yearold florida jurist claimed in a 95page motion that 
15 of the 17 counts against him should be dismissed based on his 
acquittal in a 1983 trial and the length of time since then in 
bringing the impeachment proceedings against him 
in its bill of impeachment the house accused hastings of 
conspiring with a washington attorney to receive a 150000 payoff 
in exchange for a guarantee that two racketeers would not serve time 
in prison 
hastings the first black federal official ever to be impeached 
was acquitted in a 1983 trial on that charge but the articles of 
impeachment also accuse him of making false statements and 
fabricating evidence in that proceeding 
the only article of impeachment which hastings didnt seek to 
have dismissed is one which accuses him of disclosing secret wiretap 
information in an unrelated investigation to steve clark the mayor 
of dade county fla 
in his motion with the senate hastings contended through 
attorneys that an impeachment trial on 15 of the 17 motions 
constitutes double jeopardy in view of his acquittal by a criminal 
court jury and also denies him due process because witnesses have 
died and records have been lost since then 
the motion seeks dismissal of the final 17th article on grounds 
that it is a catchall count aimed at allowing the senate to 
remove hastings from the bench with a finding that he is unfit even 
if a majority finds him innocent on each of the 16 other articles 
the house has until march 3 to file a brief in reply to hastings 
motion monday no date for oral arguments on the motion has been set 
the senate rules committee earlier this month ordered that 
arguments on the anticipated motions be heard by the full senate 
even though only a 12member panel of senators will conduct the 
evidence hearings which are expected to take about six weeks 
