all the older tappers seem to have nicknames i havent heard 
my real name in i dont know when sims said jimmy slyde whos 
in both tap and black and blue specialized in sliding 
bunny briggs 66 with his saucer eyes and bambilike lashes dances 
in both tap and black and blue he got his nickname from his 
grandmother because when shed come home from work bunny would 
quickly scoot to get her slippers 
i danced as soon as i was born he said when i saw bill 
robinson dance i knew i wanted to be a dancer he sanctioned it 
briggs tapped with big bands as a visual addition and an added 
rhythm instrument 
the earliest forms of tap dancing can be found centuries ago in 
parts of africa and ireland it was further distilled in the united 
states by african slaves and the immigrants who brought their clog 
dancing with them to the new world 
