<TEXT>
it may seem like just a day off but next monday 
marks a key ritual for affirming the nations identity by linking up 
to a legend 
with its ancestor worship and retelling of myths washingtons 
birthday serves the cultural purpose of instructing the young and 
reminding grownups about what it is to be an american social 
science experts say 
he was in a way an ideal american and so in celebrating his 
birthday the society celebrates itself it is important for society 
to do that because in this way it reinforces its values said liah 
greenfeld an assistant professor of sociology and social studies at 
harvard university 
american identity for the most part begins with washington 
said david kertzer an anthropology professor at bowdoin college in 
brunswick maine he is the point of reference for what it means 
to be an american 
george washington was born feb 22 1732 but the federal 
observance falls on feb 20 this year some states combine the 
holiday with abraham lincolns feb 12 birthday and call it 
presidents day 
ancestor worship is common in the worlds cultures the experts 
said 
enshrining heroes in myths is a way of really providing our own 
identity by attaching ourselves to a past that is larger than 
life to do that we have to regularly have some ritual observances 
to keep those myths and those heroes alive said kertzer author 
of the recent ritual politics and power 
even if many americans see washingtons birthday as just a chance 
for a threeday weekend it still does its cultural job said martha 
ward professor of anthropology and urban studies at the university 
of new orleans 
a good ritual does not have to have many participants to work 
and they dont have to be enthusiastic she said have you ever 
been to a funeral in which you were secretly cheering 
the important thing is that somebody observes the ritual ward 
said our personal feelings about this are totally immaterial 
these structures existed before we were born and they will continue 
after we are dead 
the holiday is observed more directly in schools where it 
instructs the young said richard peterson sociology professor at 
vanderbilt university 
so what does george washington represent 
theres honesty as in the cherry tree confession and strength 
as in flinging the silver dollar across the potomac river 
he also is portrayed as a loving and caring father of the country 
people need fathers this is a myth about how fathers should 
act said ward adding that the valley forge legend provides a 
classic hero myth 
heroes must go through a time of testing in which they must 
triumph they have to have followers and they have to have a sort of 
vision even if its not shared at the time with other people of 
what theyre doing 
people want to know george washington couldnt get supplies 
from the continental congress and isnt that typical the vision of 
great leaders is not shared by the legislature this is sort of a 
basic american myth about what kind of society do we have and how 
did it come into being 
yet washington is the statesman with the formal wig as well as 
the revolutionary leader said kertzer you dont think of a 
heated personality sort of a rabble rouser like lenin by 
remembering washington as a statesmanrevolutionary we deal with 
the ambiguity of our notion of a nation that was born with 
revolution and yet a nation that is very conservative 
for that purpose he said washingtons perfect 
