a month in the absence of any timepieces 
has altered the waking and sleep patterns of an italian woman whos 
spending five months in a cave to simulate the experiences of 
astronauts on long voyages 
stefania follini who entered a 100squarefoot plexiglas cubicle 
in lost cave on jan 13 has been sleeping 10 hours and staying 
awake 20 said maurizio montalbini leader of the usitalian 
research team those cycles likely will lengthen more said 
montalbini who once spent seven months in a cave 
since jan 13 the ancona italy interior designers only 
contact with the outside world has been through a personal computer 
on which she relays results of tests of concentration and brainwave 
activity 
her concentration also seems to have sharpened during her first 
weeks of isolation said montalbini who chose a cave in the united 
states for the tests because he wanted to be close to researchers 
from the national aeronautics and space administration and 
universities 
