<TEXT>
here are some shopping pointers to keep in mind if youre 
5feet4 or less and prefer not to dress like someones little girl 
study your proportions if you have a long torso and short legs 
choose long skirts and shoes with heels if you have a short torso 
and long legs then pick something like a long tunic to make the 
waist appear longer the idea is to visually soften and blend the 
proportions 
a key fitting point is at the shoulders collars and necklines 
shouldnt bunch up alterations are simpler for other parts of the 
garment if you start with a proportional shoulder fit 
choose softer versions of classically tailored suits the details 
should be scaled down with narrowed lapels and onebutton closures 
jackets cut at hipbone length will look most natural with a smaller 
frame 
shoulder pads make the waist look smaller by extending the line 
of the shoulders but make sure theyre not too big and bulky 
horizontal lines will make you look chunky so avoid square 
necklines or horizontal stripes or seams by contrast verticals 
vnecks vertical stripes and seams will smooth and narrow your 
lines 
let color help too monochromatic colors will help you maintain 
an unbroken visual line you could match hosiery and pumps to solid 
colors in pants or skirts 
keep your accessories in proportion pass up wide belts and 
overlarge handbags use your briefcase to transport extra items 
shoes with medium heels will look best avoid the extremes of 
stilletos or flats 
avoid fussy or cute touches like peter pan collars puffed 
sleeves big bows or ruffles or extravagant costume jewelry 
stand up and be confident good posture and selfassurance has a 
lot to do with how well you look in your clothes 
the tips come from the crafted with pride in usa council 
inc which represents about 400 manufacturers 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

